Ethekwini Municipality’s Cleansing and Solid Waste Unit (DSW) staff will be working throughout the festive season including Christmas day and New Year’s day and while it is the season of giving, DSW staff are strictly prohibited from touting for gifts, including money, from residents. EThekwini Municipality’s acting head of communications, Mandla Nsele, said that residents are advised to be wary of impostors posing as municipal workers to solicit gifts.“DSW’s operational services will continue as normal during the festive season including the public holidays. The public are urged to put out their refuse as early as possible to assist in this regard,” Nsele sad. The DSW offices will be closed on 16, 25 and 26 December 2019 and 1 January 2020. However, refuse collection will continue throughout the festive season, including the public holidays. For enquiries, contact the DSW help line on 031 311 8804.